result.execSummary:
The defendant Duane C. Patz was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case. On one or more other charges, Duane C. Patz was found not guilty. These charges were not proven and have no legal effect. Duane C. Patz is presumed innocent of the not guilty charges.

  • Duane C. Patz was found guilty of 1st-Degree Recklessly Endangering Safety, a class F felony, Wisconsin Statutes 941.30(1).
  • Duane C. Patz was found guilty of Strangulation and Suffocation, a class H felony, Wisconsin Statutes 940.235(1).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.
